Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@spaghetti{180%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or
use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2} (see ingredients for
amount). Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into
1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot,
add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every
couple of mins. Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer
the courgette to a #bowl{}. Wipe out the frying pan.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{225%g}. Heat another drizzle of oil in the
frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the prawns and stir-fry for
~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Meanwhile, add the spaghetti to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook
until tender, ~{8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back
in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the garlic and @dried rosemary{1%sachet} to the frying pan and cook for
~{1%minute} more, then stir through the @creme fraiche{150%g},
@vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for
amount). Bring to the boil, then lower the heat to a simmer. Cook the sauce
until thickened slightly and the prawns are cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

Add the spaghetti, courgette and half of the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) to the pan and mix well.

Squeeze some lemon juice and add a pinch of lemon zest to the pasta. Taste and
season with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed. Add a splash of water
to the sauce if it's looking a little thick.

Share the creamy prawn spaghetti between your #bowls{} and sprinkle over the
remaining cheese. Enjoy!